sor.","type":"text"}]},{"text":"Full Document Context","type":"heading","anchor":"Full-Document-Context","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Apple’s native text document proxy doesn’t return all the text within the document. It instead cuts off the available text at any time, e.g. at the previous or next paragraph. This makes it hard to provide "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/AI-Article","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" that require more context.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"KeyboardKit Pro therefore unlocks ways to read ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"all"}]},{"text":" text from the proxy, using ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/UIKit\/UITextDocumentProxy\/fullDocumentContext(config:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" proxy extensions that reads the full document content by moving the input cursor in intricate ways."}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["let proxy = keyboardContext.textDocumentProxy","let result = try await proxy.fullDocumentContext(config: ...)"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This will provide you with all the text before and after the text input cursor, as well as an aggregate of all the available text. Note that it’s a best effort operation that is not guaranteed to return a valid result. You can therefore configure the function to yield better results.","type":"text"}]}]}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/Essentials-Article","doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/Actions-Article","doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/AI-Article","doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/App-